Moving the cursor by word does not produce correct results when the text contains Chinese characters.  Currently, it seems to move character-by-character, but instead it should move word by word.

| Incorrect Flutter behavior | Correct Mac behavior |
| --- | --- |
| <video src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/389558/213824760-b7b35d2b-f762-4dfa-92c3-c1d6de71617e.webm)" />| <video src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/389558/226982482-9a99d1ba-ddf4-420b-adaf-1af56d906b2a.mov" /> |

### Steps to reproduce

  1. Run an app with a text input, such as the one below.
  2. Enter some Chinese text containing words that are more than 1 character in length, such as the example text below.
  3. Press control+arrow left/right (or option+arrow left/right on Mac).

Expected results: The cursor moves left/right to the nearest word boundary.
Actual results: The cursor moves by one character.

<details>

<summary>Example app</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'Flutter Demo',
      home: Scaffold(
        appBar: AppBar(
          title: const Text("Demo"),
        ),
        body: const Center(
          child: Column(
            mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
            children: <Widget>[
              TextField(
              ),
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

</details>

<details>

<summary>Example Chinese text</summary>

1894年，孫文成立興中會。1895年，興中會發動乙未廣州起義。1905年，中國同盟會在日本东京組成，孫被推為总理；確定「驅除韃虜，恢復中华，建立民國，平均地權」的革命政綱，提出三民主義學說；創辦《民報》，宣傳革命，同當時的中國改良派激烈論戰。

Source: https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/106472#issuecomment-1465077065

</details>

### Next steps

Does [icu](https://github.com/unicode-org/icu) have built-in support for finding Chinese word breaks?  Does SkParagraph?

Flutter may need to include a Chinese dictionary at some level for this to work.  This must be able to be tree-shaken out, because I assume the size would be non-trivial.

If that is not practical, maybe we should move between punctuation marks instead?

### Related

This is a continuation of https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/106472.

