@rydmike Yes, sorry for the churn, but the raw methods have been marked in the documentation as "going to be deprecated" for a while now (years), and we really need to remove the duplicate system to reduce the tech debt of maintaining them both, or it will just grow over time (as it already has).

There will definitely be an extensive migration guide and, for the things we can use it for, `dart fix` solutions.

The replacements are generally found linked in the existing class documentation.  For the ones you mentioned, `RawKeyboardListener` is replaced by `KeyboardListener`, and (hopefully) the information in the platform specific classes you mentioned is available in `KeyEvent`, because the platform-specific data classes are being phased out. If not, please let us know what is missing.

