    return content;
  }
```

@gspencergoog I noticed the planned removal scheduled of the deprecated `RawKeyboardListener` and related APIs was already in Q4 2024. We discovered a severe blocking issue for migrating to the new APIs last weekend and I submitted this report today https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/162305.

For **game dev** the issue is like @spydon also commented quite severe. We actually had to revert our already migrated usage to the old API, to make our game platform usable on web builds.

We kindly ask if you can hold off the removal of the deprecated `RawKeyboardListener` and its related APIs, until this issue is resolved and its fix has landed in the Flutter stable channel. Either via next stable release or as a CP:d hot-fix.

