@gspencergoog It looks like the cause of this assertion is that inactive Navigator pages are a part of the focus traversal.  So in the repro code (pasted below), the "root" page is not shown, but pressing tab traverses to it.  Since it's not laid out, it triggers the assertion.

```dart
Navigator(
  pages: <MaterialPage<Object>>[
    MaterialPage<Object>(name: 'root', child: Container()),
    const MaterialPage<Object>(name: 'panel', child: Text('Then press tab')),
  ],
  ...
),
```

Does that sound like an accurate assessment to you?  I assume the solution would be to exclude inactive pages somewhere?

